Wave 13.2 NO_INPUT_POLL ablation on real HW (PODP 5V83, Cirrus + UNIVBE)
measured the per-pump DOS_Yield() at ~115 ms / flip — the cooperative-
thread round-trip into the audio thread's WaitDevice spin
(SDL_dosaudio_sb.c:189), not the keyboard/mouse drain.

Default-skip the yield. The doskutsu engine pairs this with an explicit
SDL_Delay(0) once per flip in Renderer::flip() to keep the audio thread
scheduled — at 15 fps that's ~67 ms between yields, well under one
audio chunk's worth of buffer (186 ms at 22050 Hz stereo S16, default
4096-frame chunk size).

Set SDL_HINT_DOSKUTSU_FORCE_PUMP_YIELD=1 in the env to restore the
original per-pump yield (debug fallback if audio glitches).

Predicted impact: title scene 5.5 fps → ~15 fps on PODP 5V83.

See docs/PHASE9-NEXT-WAVES-PLAN.md §6 wave 13.2 ablation table.
---
 src/video/dos/SDL_dosevents.c | 22 +++++++++++++++++-----
 1 file changed, 17 insertions(+), 5 deletions(-)

diff --git a/src/video/dos/SDL_dosevents.c b/src/video/dos/SDL_dosevents.c
index 78a50b649..22906c6b6 100644
--- a/src/video/dos/SDL_dosevents.c
+++ b/src/video/dos/SDL_dosevents.c
@@ -254,11 +254,23 @@ static int keyevents_tail = 0;
 
 void DOSVESA_PumpEvents(SDL_VideoDevice *device)
 {
-    /* Give cooperative threads a chance to run.  Audio mixing now runs
-       in its own cooperative thread (via SDL's normal audio thread),
-       so it will execute during this yield along with loading threads
-       and anything else that is runnable. */
-    DOS_Yield();
+    /* DOSKUTSU patch (Phase 9 wave 13.3): the per-pump DOS_Yield() was
+       measured at ~115 ms / flip on real HW (PODP 5V83, Cirrus + UNIVBE)
+       — see docs/PHASE9-NEXT-WAVES-PLAN.md §6 wave 13.2 ablation results.
+       Cost is the cooperative-thread round-trip into the audio thread's
+       WaitDevice spin (SDL_dosaudio_sb.c:189), not the keyboard/mouse
+       drain below. Default-skip the yield here; the engine is expected
+       to call SDL_Delay(0) once per flip to keep the audio thread
+       scheduled. Set SDL_HINT_DOSKUTSU_FORCE_PUMP_YIELD=1 in the env to
+       restore the original behavior (debug fallback if audio glitches). */
+    static int yield_skip_cached = -1;
+    if (yield_skip_cached == -1) {
+        const char *force = SDL_getenv("SDL_HINT_DOSKUTSU_FORCE_PUMP_YIELD");
+        yield_skip_cached = (force && force[0] == '1' && force[1] == 0) ? 0 : 1;
+    }
+    if (!yield_skip_cached) {
+        DOS_Yield();
+    }
 
     static bool is_extended = false;
     static int pause_sequence_remaining = 0;
